  "description": {
    "en": "Brown bears are large, powerful predators distributed across North America, Europe, and Asia.",
    "zh": "棕熊是大型且强壮的捕食者，广泛分布于北美洲、欧洲和亚洲。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Brown bears are among the largest land predators on Earth, with males weighing up to 600 kilograms. They have a distinctive muscular hump on their shoulders that gives them powerful digging strength. Their fur color ranges from blonde to dark brown, and they have long, curved claws that can be over 10 centimeters long.",
      "zh": "棕熊是地球上最大的陆地捕食者之一，雄性体重可达600公斤。它们的肩膀上有一个独特的肌肉隆起，这给了它们强大的挖掘力量。它们的毛色从金黄色到深棕色不等，弯曲的爪子可以超过10厘米长。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Brown bears are omnivores that eat berries, roots, fish, and small mammals. They are famous for catching salmon as the fish leap up waterfalls during spawning season. In winter, brown bears hibernate in dens for several months, living off the fat they stored during autumn.",
      "zh": "棕熊是杂食动物，吃浆果、根茎、鱼和小型哺乳动物。它们最出名的就是在鲑鱼产卵季节，在瀑布旁抓住跳跃的鲑鱼。冬天时，棕熊会在洞穴中冬眠好几个月，靠秋天储存的脂肪维生。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Brown bears live in forests, mountains, and river valleys across North America, Europe, and Asia. In North America, they are commonly found in Alaska and western Canada. The grizzly bear, a well-known subspecies, lives in the Rocky Mountains and Pacific Northwest.",
      "zh": "棕熊生活在北美洲、欧洲和亚洲的森林、山脉和河谷地带。在北美洲，它们常见于阿拉斯加和加拿大西部。灰熊是一种著名的亚种，生活在落基山脉和太平洋西北地区。"
    }
  },
